  "prompt": "What are the types of writing styles? How are they used?",
  "response": "Here are the main types of writing styles:\n\n1. Narrative Writing\n- Tells a story\n- Uses descriptive language\n- Often found in fiction, novels, short stories\n- Includes characters, plot, and dialogue\n\n2. Descriptive Writing\n- Focuses on detailed descriptions\n- Paints vivid pictures with words\n- Used in poetry, travel writing, and creative works\n- Emphasizes sensory details and imagery\n\n3. Expository Writing\n- Explains or informs\n- Presents facts objectively\n- Used in textbooks, news articles, scientific papers\n- Focuses on clarity and information\n\n4. Persuasive Writing\n- Aims to convince or argue a point\n- Uses logical reasoning and emotional appeals\n- Common in editorials, opinion pieces, marketing\n- Presents arguments and supports claims\n\n5. Technical Writing\n- Provides instructions or detailed information\n- Used in manuals, scientific documents, guides\n- Focuses on clarity and precision\n- Uses specialized language\n\n6. Academic Writing\n- Scholarly and research-based\n- Follows specific formatting and citation rules\n- Used in research papers, dissertations\n- Emphasizes objectivity and critical analysis\n\n7. Creative Writing\n- Focuses on originality and artistic expression\n- Includes fiction, poetry, scripts\n- Prioritizes imagination and emotional impact\n\nEach style serves different purposes and is used in various contexts.",
